<taxonomicName box="[1372,1436,476,499]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1372,1436,476,499]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Pinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
? 
<emphasis box="[163,241,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">jeffreyi</emphasis>
and from chapparal habitats in Inyo, Los Angeles, Placer, Riverside, San Benito, San Diego, Santa Barbara, Santa Clara and Stanislaus counties (
<collectionCode box="[689,765,547,571]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">RLZC</collectionCode>
, 
<collectionCode box="[780,862,547,571]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/m2jc-wmeq" name="University of California, Riverside" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">UCRC</collectionCode>
). Another specimen that may be referable to this genus was collected in Solano County (
<collectionCode box="[593,677,583,607]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/kd99-229r" name="R. M. Bohart Museum of Entomology" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">UCDC</collectionCode>
